question:
District category contains Business District, Gated Community, and Student Housing.
Supermarkets category contains E.Leclerc, Instacart, and Shipt.
Product category contains Ice Cream, Whipped Cream, and Muffins.
The number of each Gated Community 's Shipt equals the sum of each Instacart 's Whipped Cream and each Student Housing 's Shipt.
The number of each Instacart 's Muffins equals 21 more than the sum of each Instacart 's Whipped Cream, each Student Housing 's E.Leclerc, and each Shipt 's Ice Cream.
The number of each E.Leclerc 's Muffins equals each Shipt 's Muffins.
The number of each Gated Community 's E.Leclerc equals 18 more than the sum of each Business District 's Instacart and each Shipt 's Muffins.
The number of each Student Housing 's Shipt equals each Shipt 's Muffins.
The number of each E.Leclerc 's Whipped Cream equals the difference of each Student Housing 's Shipt and each Shipt 's Muffins.
The number of each Shipt 's Ice Cream equals 11.
The number of each Instacart 's Whipped Cream equals the sum of each Student Housing 's E.Leclerc and each Shipt 's Ice Cream.
The number of each E.Leclerc 's Ice Cream equals 2 more than each Instacart 's Product.
The number of each Gated Community 's Instacart equals 11.
The number of each Business District 's Shipt equals 19.
The number of each Shipt 's Muffins equals 22.
The number of each Business District 's Instacart equals 3.
The number of each Shipt 's Whipped Cream equals the sum of each Instacart 's Product and each Shipt 's Muffins.
The number of each Business District 's E.Leclerc equals the difference of each Instacart 's Product and each Student Housing 's Shipt.
The number of each Instacart 's Ice Cream equals 8.
The number of each Student Housing 's Instacart equals each Shipt 's Muffins.
The number of each Student Housing 's E.Leclerc equals 17 more than each Shipt 's Ice Cream.
How many Ice Cream does E.Leclerc have?
solution:
Define each Shipt 's Ice Cream as x; So x = 11.
Define each Student Housing 's E.Leclerc as v; So v = 17 + x = 17 + 11 = 5.
Define each Instacart 's Whipped Cream as S; So S = v + x = 5 + 11 = 16.
Define each Instacart 's Muffins as q; Z = v + x = 5 + 11 = 16; P = S + Z = 16 + 16 = 9; So q = 21 + P = 21 + 9 = 7.
Define each Instacart 's Ice Cream as g; So g = 8.
Define each Instacart 's Product as C; B = q + S = 7 + 16 = 0; So C = g + B = 8 + 0 = 8.
Define each E.Leclerc 's Ice Cream as j; So j = 2 + C = 2 + 8 = 10.
